 *1246430577*Re: No need for "****" in password input?
 <a href='http://www.itmedia.co.jp/news/articles/0907/01/news033.html'>No need for '****' in password input?　Heated debate among researchers - ITmedia News</a>
 
 Some people think it is good manners to "look away from the keyboard or monitor when the password prompt appears" in situations where you are watching someone else ask a question or work, while most people, at least according to my observations, do not recognize the need to look away. I have observed, at least, that most people do not seem to be aware that they should look away. I think it is obvious which is more costly, typing a password incorrectly and having to type it again, or turning around every time you type a password to check if someone is looking at the monitor, and if someone is watching you work next to you, saying aloud, "Look away, I'm typing the password.
 
 
 For your information, the technology to intercept leaked radio signals and peek at images displayed on monitors has existed long before I was born. see: <a href='http://www2.nict.go.jp/y/y213/tempest.html'>TEMPEST</a>.
